reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bang for your buck
reviews.reviewText: This is an amazing, affordable item for a home office. There's enough surface area to operate 2-3 screens simultaneously. Set up was a breeze, very easy to read instructions. Total assembly time was around 40 min. (taking my sweet time). Definitely would recommend to the gamer, audio engineer, and from home folks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality// biggest bang for your buck
reviews.reviewText: I usually don’t write reviews but this is the SECOND desk I’ve bought from this company. BOTH are In fantastic shape one I’ve had for over a year and the second I just got, more than likely will be buying a third soon. The wood on this piece is BEAUTIFUL ✨ very sturdy, I have my PC on my desk in the other setup (that’s how much I trust this) the standing feature is amazing. I know people who have spent $1500+ on a worse desk and this one was $98 when I got mine. 1000000% worth the purchase!!!! BUY IT!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: It's a great table! It did arrive with a few chips and dings unfortunately on the top front of the table where it'll be visible but I after buying two I can see it's the shipping where that happens. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars What a WASTE of Money
reviews.reviewText: I mean, I don't even know where to begin! The assembly instructions were incredibly vague, and the wimpiest little hexagonal wrench was all that was provided - even still, not that big of a deal. I push forward, assembling the pieces exactly as instructed, only to find that the two pieces for the top of the desk literally cannot fit onto the assembled stand without creating new drill holes, as they were not measured out properly. And yes, I tried every which way to ensure I was not, in fact, the idiot of the situation. No luck. Still, I forge ahead. Once everything is assembled and I test this baby out - I give that up button a whirl and hear the smooth automated sound of the gears working to raise the desk up, up....UP! It had a three second delay after releasing the button that caused it to nearly wedge itself under my windowsill. ZERO safety features for this thing, which would be fine if the machine actually stopped when you let off the button. Alas. When I decided to return it, I was offered either a partial refund without returning it, or a full refund with return. I chose the full refund option, but was unable to find a box that could actually fit the pieces to return (the original box was made of such weak cardboard that it was beyond reuse), and reached out to a representative to get the previously offered partial refund. However, because I cancelled my return before reaching out to support and the date for my return window had passed, it was now magically no one's problem. So no customer support, no functional desk, and not even a partial refund to show for it. Ew.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars You get what you pay for...
reviews.reviewText: First the good about this desk. The up/down motor works fine. It has three presets, and is easy to set. The work surface is fairly thin, but is fine for a desk.Now the bad. The installation is a pain. The quality control clearly does not review the end product. Almost all of the screw holes were not in the right place. This meant that there was a large gap between the two panels. It also meant that securing the top to the legs required new holes to be drilled. If you raise the desk to a standing height, it is not the most stable with some wiggling. The desk is priced low, but that is most likely due to the items I mentioned. Not recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great price for a great desk
reviews.reviewText: Bout this fit my office set up and it was right at $90. Easy to set up only took me about 30 minutes. One person job. Clean seat. No damage during shipping. Low noise when raising it up and down. If you’re looking for a clean standing desk or just looking for an upgrade, this desk is for you. Bang for your buck
